2026-07-05 - assets/scss/_components.scss: Added .article_excerpt blockquote override
  (strip quote-icon background/padding and inline margins) so the homepage hero
  teaser renders blockquote-led post summaries as normal flowing text instead of
  a narrow, tall column.
2026-07-05 - assets/scss/_components.scss: Added margin-bottom to paragraphs inside
  .article_excerpt blockquote to restore the visual gap between a quoted line and
  its attribution line in the hero teaser (previously only provided by .post p
  padding on the full post page).
2026-07-05 - assets/scss/_components.scss: Added, then later removed, a
  .lg-outer .lg-thumb-outer padding-top !important override intended to add space
  between the displayed image and the lightGallery thumbnail strip. Superseded by
  the allowMediaOverlap fix below; removed because it was offsetting individual
  thumbnail images down within their boxes.
2026-07-05 - layouts/partials/footer.html: Changed lightGallery's allowMediaOverlap
  option from true to false so the displayed image is sized to leave room for the
  caption and thumbnail strip, stacked without overlapping (title now appears below
  the image and above the thumbnails).
2026-07-05 - assets/scss/_components.scss: Added .lg-thumb-item img { margin: 0; }
  override to fix a pre-existing bug (present in production) where the site's
  global `img { margin: 15px auto; }` rule in _base.scss was pushing lightGallery
  thumbnail images down within their fixed-height, overflow-hidden boxes, leaving a
  blank band at the top of every thumbnail.
2026-07-05 - assets/scss/_components.scss: Added .lg-outer .lg-sub-html
  { padding-top: 25px; } to add breathing room between the displayed image and
  its caption (tried 5px first, too subtle; 25px confirmed as the right amount).
2026-07-05 - assets/scss/_components.scss: Added .lg-outer .lg-sub-html
  { color: var(--dark); } so the caption text (previously light gray/white,
  #eee from vendor CSS) is readable now that the backdrop is white.
2026-07-05 - assets/scss/_components.scss: Added .lg-container .lg-backdrop
  { background-color: #fff; } to change the gallery's full-screen backdrop
  from black to white, overriding the vendored rule via a more specific
  selector (no !important, no vendor file edits).
2026-07-05 - assets/scss/_components.scss: Added .lg-container .lg-outer
  .lg-thumb-outer { background-color: #fff; } to match the thumbnail strip's
  background to the new white backdrop, same higher-specificity technique.
2026-07-05 - Investigated why the thumbnail show/hide toggle button
  disappeared after the allowMediaOverlap change: the vendor plugin
  (lg-thumbnail.umd.js) explicitly disables toggleThumb whenever
  allowMediaOverlap is false, since toggling wouldn't resize the image with
  overlap off anyway. Decision: keep allowMediaOverlap: false and live without
  the toggle button rather than reintroduce the caption/image overlap. No code
  change made.
2026-07-05 - assets/scss/_components.scss: Added a responsive
  .lg-container .lg-outer .lg-img-wrap override (left/right: 15px, width:
  calc(100% - 30px) by default; 80px/calc(100% - 160px) from 768px width up)
  so the displayed image can never grow wide enough to sit directly under the
  prev/next arrow buttons, with a smaller inset on phones so the image isn't
  overly cramped.
2026-07-05 - assets/scss/_components.scss: Restyled the prev/next buttons
  (.lg-container .lg-next / .lg-prev) to remove the vendor's gray box
  background/padding/border-radius, enlarged the arrow glyph, and set its
  color to var(--dark) (var(--theme) on hover) so they read as plain arrows
  against the white backdrop instead of barely-legible gray rectangles.
2026-07-05 - layouts/shortcodes/gallery.html: Added support for an opt-in
  `break: true` field on an imglist entry, which emits an empty
  .post_gallery_break div right after that thumbnail.
2026-07-05 - assets/scss/_posts.scss: Added .post_gallery_break { flex-basis:
  100%; height: 0; }, a zero-height full-width flex item that forces the post
  gallery's thumbnail grid to start a new row at that point, giving manual
  control over how many thumbnails appear per row.
2026-07-05 - assets/scss/_posts.scss: Added a scoped `.post ul { list-style:
  disc; padding: 1rem 1.25rem 1rem 2.25rem; }` rule so markdown bullet lists
  in post content (e.g. content/post/jazz-adjacent.md) display their bullets
  again. The global `ul { list-style: none; }` reset in _base.scss (meant for
  nav menus) was stripping them; `ol` already had an equivalent post-scoped
  padding override but `ul` did not.
2026-07-07 - layouts/shortcodes/exhibit.html: New shortcode, modeled on
  gallery.html, for posts that want their on-page images shown at the wider
  -0450.jpg resolution instead of gallery's -0240.jpg thumbnail. Reuses
  gallery's id='lightgallery' and lightbox href/data-srcset so the existing
  lightGallery init code and CSS keep working unchanged.
2026-07-07 - layouts/shortcodes/exhibit.html + assets/scss/_posts.scss: Gave
  exhibit its own post_exhibit / post_exhibit_break classes (previously
  reused gallery's post_gallery / post_gallery_break) and a matching
  &_exhibit block in _posts.scss, so its layout could diverge from
  gallery.html's without touching gallery's CSS. Container capped at
  max-width: 930px !important, with each thumbnail <a> forced to
  calc(50% - 1rem) width (two per row, with a 1rem gap) and its <img> scaled
  to width: 100% of that column.
2026-07-07 - layouts/shortcodes/exhibit.html + assets/scss/_posts.scss: Added
  an opt-in `small: true` field for imglist entries, matching the existing
  `break: true` convention. Flagged entries get class='small' on their <a>,
  overridden in CSS to calc(33.33% - 1rem) width, letting three small images
  sit side by side within the same 930px container that otherwise shows two
  full-width images per row. (Briefly tried widening the container to 1410px
  to fit three full-width images per row, and separately tried scaling the
  default/small anchor widths to 33.33%/18.15% for that wider container, but
  a higher-level layout div constrains the available width, so both of those
  changes were reverted back to max-width: 930px and the default 50% anchor
  width; only the small-image width setting was kept, changed to
  calc(33.33% - 1rem) so three small images fill a 930px row.)
2026-07-07 - assets/scss/_posts.scss: Fixed the exhibit thumbnail grid
  appearing shifted left of center. Cause: each <a>'s `padding: 0 1rem 1rem 0`
  only added a gap-simulating margin on its own right/bottom side, so the
  last item in a row had a trailing padding gap with nothing after it to
  balance, throwing off `justify-content: center`'s math. Replaced the
  per-anchor padding with `gap: 1rem` on the .post_exhibit container (which
  never adds trailing space) and rebalanced column widths to
  calc(50% - 0.5rem) (default, two per row) and calc((100% - 2rem) / 3)
  (small, three per row) so N columns plus their gaps sum to exactly 100%.
2026-07-07 - assets/scss/_posts.scss: Changed .post_exhibit a img from a
  forced `width: 100%` to `max-width: 100%` plus `margin: 0 auto`, so an
  image never renders larger than its native resolution. Needed because
  -0450.jpg files preserve aspect ratio by capping the *longest* edge at
  450px, so a portrait image's native width is well under 450px; forcing
  width: 100% of a column sized for a 450px-wide landscape image stretched
  those portrait images past their native size.
2026-07-07 - assets/scss/_posts.scss: Added `min-width: 0` to .post_exhibit a
  to override the flex item's default `min-width: auto`, which otherwise
  prevents a flex item from shrinking below the intrinsic width of an image
  inside it — relevant for the narrower `small` columns.
2026-07-07 - layouts/shortcodes/exhibit.html: Found the actual cause of the
  three-small-images-overlapping bug: `small: true` entries were still
  loading the full -0450.jpg file for the on-page thumbnail, so the browser
  was laying out full-resolution (450px-wide) images inside ~299px columns
  regardless of the CSS width/gap/min-width fixes above. Changed the
  template so small-flagged entries load -0240.jpg instead for the on-page
  <img> (the lightbox's href/data-srcset are unchanged, still using the full
  -0450/-0900/-1200/-1920 variants).
2026-07-08 - assets/scss/_variables.scss: Removed the
  `@media (prefers-color-scheme: dark)` rule so every page always renders in
  light mode, regardless of the visitor's OS/browser dark-mode setting.
  Cause: this project's own layouts/partials/nav.html override never
  includes the theme's manual dark-mode toggle (themes/newsroom/layouts/
  partials/mode.html), so dark mode was only ever triggered automatically by
  system preference — reported after a visitor's iPad (set to dark mode)
  showed a black site background behind lightGallery's still-white viewer,
  which has no dark-mode awareness at all. The dormant `[data-mode="dark"]`
  rule/mixin was left in place (harmless; unreachable without a toggle
  control) in case a manual toggle is added back later.
2026-07-08 - assets/scss/_nav.scss: Changed .nav from `position: absolute` to
  `position: fixed` so the header stays visible while scrolling long pages
  instead of scrolling away with the content. No other layout changes were
  needed since the header was already out of normal document flow, with
  manually-tuned clearance margins elsewhere (.mt, .mt-6, .pt-6) already
  accounting for that.
2026-07-08 - assets/scss/_nav.scss: Added `background-color: var(--bg)` to
  .nav, which previously had no background at all (fully transparent) —
  necessary now that the header is fixed in place and page content scrolls
  underneath it.
2026-07-08 - assets/scss/_base.scss: Added `html { -webkit-text-size-adjust:
  100%; }`, an attempted fix for blockquote indentation (5rem on .post
  blockquote plus 4rem on the inner p) appearing much wider on an iPhone
  (both Safari and Chrome for iOS, which share the same WebKit engine) than
  on iPad/desktop. Theory was WebKit's automatic root-font-size inflation on
  narrow viewports, since the indent is entirely rem-based. CONFIRMED
  INEFFECTIVE — user reported no change on the phone. A second theory (OS-
  level "Larger Text" accessibility setting affecting the unset <html>
  root font-size) was also ruled out by testing. Root cause remains
  unidentified; left in place as a harmless, generally-correct default, but
  it did not resolve the reported issue. Investigation paused without a
  fix — revisit with actual device screenshots or Safari Web Inspector
  measurements if picked back up.
2026-07-08 - assets/scss/_variables.scss + assets/scss/_posts.scss: Added a
  dedicated `--link` CSS variable and pointed `.post_inner a` at it instead
  of `--theme` (#808080), so link color can be tuned independently of
  `--theme`'s other uses (tag backgrounds, nav hover, lightGallery arrow
  hover). Iterated through several values live (#4d4d4d, #303030, #000000,
  and #ff0000 as a diagnostic to confirm .post_inner a was the correct rule)
  before landing on navy, `--link: #000080`. Also added `font-weight: bold;`
  to `.post_inner a`. Along the way, confirmed (by turning --theme blue and
  finding regular body text unaffected) that body text color comes from
  `body { color: var(--text) }` in _base.scss, unrelated to `--theme`.
2026-07-09 - assets/scss/_variables.scss: Changed `--link` from navy
  (#000080) to black (#000), keeping the bold weight set previously.
2026-07-09 - assets/scss/_nav.scss: Fixed the header (title/subtitle/email
  vs. the nav_bar hamburger icon) not staying centered on the page at wide
  viewports. Root cause: `.nav { position: fixed; width: 100% }` was
  resolving its 100% against `body`'s box (`max-width: 1440px; margin: 0
  auto`, which is narrower than and offset from the real viewport once the
  window exceeds 1440px) rather than the true browser viewport — a real
  browser quirk with fixed-position descendants of a width-constrained,
  auto-centered ancestor, confirmed by isolating minimal repro cases outside
  the site. Fixed by switching `.nav` to `width: 100vw; left: 0;`, which
  anchors it to the actual viewport regardless of body's box. Also widened
  `.nav-menu`'s `max-width` from the initial 1024px (matching `.wrap`, which
  made title and nav_bar feel too close together) to 1224px, so the header
  is a fixed ~200px wider than the `.wrap` content column and centers
  independently once the window narrows below that.
2026-07-07 - layouts/shortcodes/ai-correction.html: New shortcode extracting
  the "Use of AI image correction" section from
  content/post/turisti-e-gente-del-posto.md into a fully static, reusable
  block (per user's choice — no per-page parameters), so it can be dropped
  into other posts with {{< ai-correction >}}. The original post's inline
  section was replaced with the shortcode call.
